## Local Development Using Ansible and Vagrant for AWS-based Deployments

You know the story, and chances are if you are working with and AWS based infrastructure, you have something like this already set up.  This is likely old news for you, but I thought I'd record my version and walkthrough of setting this up.  Please go ahead and ping me below and add your favorite modifications to this scheme.

### Some Sources
* http://docs.ansible.com/ansible/guide_vagrant.html
* https://www.vagrantup.com/docs/provisioning/ansible.html
* http://docs.ansible.com/ansible/intro_installation.html#installing-the-control-machine

### The Docs
* https://www.vagrantup.com/docs/

### The Setup

* Install [Ansible](http://docs.ansible.com/ansible/intro_installation.html#installing-the-control-machine) on your Vagrant host.
* According to the Ansible documentation, your Vagrant host should ideally provide a recent version of OpenSSH that [supports ControlPersist](http://docs.ansible.com/ansible/faq.html#how-do-i-get-ansible-to-reuse-connections-enable-kerberized-ssh-or-have-ansible-pay-attention-to-my-local-ssh-config-file)
